<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1319">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Austro-Hungarian
                                Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DCT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dumba</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: In reply to your
                            letter of this morning, I find to my regret that the translation of your
                            communication to Vienna was forwarded to us from London in a secret
                            cipher, and as it is contrary to our rules to furnish the actual texts
                            of such messages, I have no other alternative than to send you a
                            paraphrase thereof.</p>
                        <p>Trusting that you will understand the reasons for my inability to comply
                            more precisely with your request, I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>